{
  "texts": [
    "For a summary of recent empirical findings and user studies in XAI research, see Vainio-Pekka et al. (2023); Rong et al. (2024).",
    "Moreover, the critical survey of Deck et al. (2023) points out a misalignment between fairness desiderata and the actual capabilities of the state-of-the-art in XAI.",
    "Decision-making processes that affect individuals' rights and freedoms often require explanation (Kroll et al., 2017) (recall Sect.",
    "\"AI fairness beyond metrics: transparency and accountability of AI systems\").",
    "While XAI methods offer a (non-exhaustive) way to hold AI systems accountable (Doshi-Velez et al., 2017), there are a number of limitations of current state-of-the-art that need to be acknowledged, and that should caution us from using these methods blindly."
  ]
}